      "message": "I don\u0027t think this was the right way to resolve this. It result should always be utf-8, independent of whether python 2 or 3 is used. \n\nThe result returned when using Python 3, happens to be utf-8, because the API returns the default for Python 3, which also happens to be utf-8.\n\nBut, I think there is a bug in the Python 2. The Python 2 result happens to be ASCII, because that is the result.\n\nI think the proper case us that both Python 2 and 3, should expect utf-8 as the result.\n\nThe result in the Versions resource, which currently does not specify utf-8, should be modified to always return utf-8.",
